notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
Several leaves more or less damaged.
A record of birth of Se'adyah ben Mosheh: inscribed, folio 157r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrash ha-ḥefets, a philosophical midrash on the Pentateuch by Zechariah ben Solomon ha-Rofe, aka Yaḥya ben Saliman.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 26 34; written lines: 26 34; Some catchwords preserved. Beginnings of chapters and sections highlighted. Frequently elongated last letter in a line to fill the space.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of 16th century. Mosheh ben Yosef ben Mosheh ben Se'adyah: inscribed, folio 157r, writing for Se'id ben Maḥapots, inscribed on the same folio.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Midrash ha-Chafets. Hebrew and Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2382.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 23 July 1881: inscribed, folio [305v].
